<body style="margin:0;padding:0;background-color:#ffffff;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;color:#27272a;">
  <div style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;padding:32px 20px;">
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Hey,</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Three weeks into the roadmap. You have the sizing, the system-type comparison, and the efficiency math. Now check the dollars-off stack before you ask for quotes.</p>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">The three layers</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 10px 0;"><strong>Federal tax credits.</strong> Some qualifying heat-pump projects may be eligible for a federal residential energy credit. The exact amount depends on the equipment and tax rules for the year you place the system in service.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 10px 0;"><strong>State programs.</strong> Some states run rebate programs with their own eligibility rules and funding windows.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 18px 0;"><strong>Utility programs.</strong> Many utilities offer separate rebates for qualifying equipment. Some require pre-approval before installation.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">The important part: do not assume your contractor will surface every program. Ask before you sign, because some rebates cannot be claimed retroactively.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">For {{ location.state }}, start with DSIRE's state-filtered database:</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 24px 0;"><a href="{{ rebate_lookup_url }}" style="color:#FF6B2B;font-weight:600;text-decoration:underline;">Check {{ location.state }} HVAC and energy-efficiency incentives</a></p>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">Contractor competence test</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 18px 0;">Ask: "Is this equipment eligible for any federal, state, or utility incentives, and will you provide the manufacturer documentation and itemized invoice I need?" A contractor who handles these projects regularly should be able to answer directly.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 24px 0;"><a href="{{ cta_url }}" style="color:#FF6B2B;font-weight:600;text-decoration:underline;">Get matched with local HVAC pros</a></p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Day 28 is the final email: how to vet contractors and collect quotes.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:20px 0 4px 0;">&mdash; NailTheQuote</p>
